Lunchtime Vegan Feast. I just made it up on the spot and it was very tasty. 
A lentil warm salad
A potato salad with a mustard kick
Hummus 
Recipe below.  It's basically made up of 3 separate dishes with various components which you can have on their own and with other meals too, I will be posting on my blog the full recipe and show you some ideas if how versatile this little lot can be! 
Make some Beanies hummus recipe here: http://www.beaniesvegankitchen.com/beanies-hummus

Pre cook some brown split lentils cooked in veg stock cube, onions and garlic. Drain. 
Pre cook some orzo with a veg stock cube, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon cayenne. Drain and stir in a tablespoon of coconut milk (the creamy bit of a tin). Pre cook some new potatoes. Drain and cool. 
Get a large bowl, defrost some peas place them in the bowl. Add some chopped fresh herbs, I used fennel oregano and rosemary from the garden. Add some chopped lettuce that's been drizzled and tossed in some freshly squeezed lemon juice. Add 1/2 small chopped red onion.  Bring it all together: Add the cooked lentils and orzo, you want them to be warm. Thoroughly mix with your hands. 
Make the dressing for the potatoes: in a small bowl add 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard, 2 tablespoons of the cream of a tin of coconut milk, 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar. Mix to a paste then gradually add some olive oil to a dressing consistency, add salt and pepper to taste. Pour over the potatoes and thoroughly coat them.

Serve and enjoy your feast!
